{
  "version": 1,
  "_comment": [
    "Cold-start knowledge for command suggestions. Everything here is a WEAK prior: an entry the player",
    "never uses decays out of the list, and one they do use becomes a real learned entry whose own count",
    "quickly dwarfs whatever is written here. A stale or wrong entry therefore costs one suggestion nobody",
    "picks, not a wrong answer anyone is stuck with — which is what makes it safe to ship a list of another",
    "server's commands at all. Players who would rather start clean can switch priors off in the",
    "Command Suggestions tab.",
    "",
    "slots  — what each argument position holds: enum (learned), player (learned if opted in), text (NEVER",
    "         learned). The last entry repeats for every further position.",
    "values — known values for the FIRST argument only.",
    "prior  — 0..1, how strongly to suggest before the player has used it.",
    "bare   — false for commands that are useless without an argument, so they do not head the list alone."
  ],

